  "recipe_notes": [
    "For best results, choose pork shoulder with some marbling for tenderness.",
    "Adjust water quantity depending on desired sauce consistency; use less for thicker sauce.",
    "Optional additions: green peas, bell peppers, or garbanzo beans for extra texture.",
    "The pork liver can be omitted if desired, though it provides authentic flavor.",
    "If the sauce becomes too thick during simmering, add hot water 1/4 cup at a time."
  ],
  "storage_notes": [
    "Store leftovers in an airtight container in the refrigerator for up to 3 days.",
    "Reheat gently on the stovetop over medium-low heat or in the microwave until heated through.",
    "Flavors develop overnight, making this dish excellent for meal prep.",
    "Not recommended for freezing due to the texture changes in potatoes and liver."
  ],
